    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Quantum entanglement is a phenomenon where two or more particles become intertwined in such a way that the state of one particle instantly influences the state of the other, no matter how far apart they are. It's a fundamental aspect of quantum mechanics that defies classical intuition. Unlike classical correlation, which is based on observable properties and can be explained by classical physics, entanglement involves non-local connections that cannot be explained by classical means. In essence, entangled particles are like a pair of magical dice that always land on the same number, even if one is in one city and the other is in another. This mysterious connection is what makes quantum entanglement so fascinating and unlike anything we see in the classical world.",
